events.description: The release of Australia's goods imports data for December 2025, showing a decline to a three-month low.

facts.fact_text: Australia’s goods imports dropped 0.8% month-on-month to AUD 41.26 billion in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Australia’s goods imports dropped 0.8% month-on-month to a three-month low of AUD 41.26 billion in December 2025

facts.fact_text: Purchases of intermediate and other merchandise goods shrank 1.3% to AUD 16.72 billion.

evidences.evidence_text: Purchases of intermediate and other merchandise goods shrank 1.3% to AUD 16.72 billion

facts.fact_text: Imports of capital goods fell 2.5% to AUD 9.65 billion.

evidences.evidence_text: Imports of capital goods also fell 2.5% to AUD 9.65 billion

facts.fact_text: Consumption goods grew 0.8% to AUD 12.64 billion.

evidences.evidence_text: In contrast, consumption goods grew 0.8% to AUD 12.64 billion

claims.claim_text: The decline in imports indicates weaker domestic demand at the end of 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The latest result indicated weaker domestic demand at the year-end

claims.claim_text: Business investment is cautious due to an uncertain global outlook.

evidences.evidence_text: cautious business investment amid an uncertain global outlook
